{
  "message": "chore(beads): track canonical beads artifacts in git\n\nProblem:\n- The repository-level .gitignore ignored .beads/ wholesale, which prevented issue graph state from ever being committed.\n- This made the project appear to have no beads in remote clones even though local planning work existed.\n\nChanges:\n- Replaced the blanket .beads/ ignore rule with targeted ignores for local runtime state only:\n  - .beads/*.db, .beads/*.db-shm, .beads/*.db-wal\n  - .beads/*.lock, .beads/last-touched, .beads/*.tmp\n- Added canonical beads artifacts to source control:\n  - .beads/config.yaml\n  - .beads/metadata.json\n  - .beads/issues.jsonl\n  - .beads/.gitignore\n\nWhy this is correct:\n- Keeps portable, collaboration-critical planning data versioned.\n- Excludes ephemeral local DB/cache/lock artifacts to avoid noise and merge churn.\n- Aligns with the br workflow expectation that JSONL-backed issue state is shared via git.",
